Variables
================

Global      => everywhere
Member      => only available to members --> in functions
Instance    => Only available to particular instance of a class --> in created instances of that class


Functions
================

Global      => everywhere
Member      => only available to members --> in functions
Instance    => Only available to particular instance of a class --> in created instances of that class


Class
===============

class DerivedClass(BaseClass):
    # code goes here

Access Methods in Superclass
+++++++++++++++++++++++++++=
class Derived(Base):
    def m(self):
    return super(Derived, self).m()
